(1)

St. Nicholas Ave., east side, south from West 169th Street, showing low structures lining a triangular area caused by the convergence of Broadway and the above Ave., and is known as Mitchell Square.

June 15, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)

A detail of same, showing mainly the N.E. corner of West 169th Street. Occupying the balance of this block and facing on the west side of Audubon Ave. is P.S. 169, the rear of which appears on the right.

June 15, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
